g.text: In nervous tissue, skeletal muscle Type II

THAN
aka transient hyperammonemia of the newborn/prematurity.
DISEASE
Unconfirmed aethiology, however "transient hyperammonemia is known to be caused by increased levels of ammonia in the blood stream, as well as a failure of the urea cycle to convert enough of the ammonia into urea." [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transient_hyperammonemia_of_the_newborn]
